:::: ABOUT EON

Eon is my collection of add-ons for GNU Emacs (version 22 or later.)
Many more files are in preparation.

:::: STATUS

2007-11-08: This is the last alpha release. Beta is next!

:::: THE FILES IN THIS ARCHIVE

  COPYING        Your license (GPL v3).
  Makefile       The makefile!
  README         The file you are reading now.
  cell.el        A generalized spreadsheet program. (UNFINISHED)
  cl-guide.el    A guide to using the CL package. (UNFINISHED)
  color-theme-eon.el --- My standard color theme.
  eon.el         Object-oriented extension to Emacs Lisp
  eon-maint.el   Used to configure batch byte-compilation of Eon.
  iso-date.el    Standard timestamping stuff
  org-blog.el    Blogging add-on for org-mode
  peano.el       Document structure/indexing tool (UNFINISHED)
  pixel.el       Very simple XPM pixel drawing app (eon demo)
  usb.el         Utilities for managing many USB storage devices

:::: HOW TO INSTALL EON

Look at the Makefile and make any changes you need. Then:

  make
  make install

:::: THEN WHAT DO I DO?

Not much; this is primarily a developer's release. There's one (not
very exciting) xpm widget demo. See the file "eon.el" (in this
archive) for further instructions.

:::: ABOUT THE METACONFERENCE                 

The Emacs Meta Activity Conference Symposium (or "metaconference"
for short) is a recurring decentralized, self-organizing,
interventionist semi-structured content-optional meta activity
event. The conference is free and open for anyone to attend.

Online conference:

 - presentations, articles, and screencasts
 - dedicated IRC channel ##metaconference for discussion
                         ^^ (two pound signs)
 - dedicated torrent for multimedia distribution?
 - lasts minutes or days
 - people in various time zones can catch up at their leisure
 - public logging and archiving of IRC "Conference Proceedings" 
   is encouraged.
 - monthly zine? i would love this

Live-action conference:

 (We haven't done this yet.)
 - presentations and demos
 - coffee (or just have the event near a coffee shop)
 - performance art
 - live streaming audio with audience feedback via IRC? (i have some
   hardware to support this)
 - rms keynote?    

More info:

irc: freenode.net#metaconference
mailing list: metaconference@emacsen.org
subscription contact: mwolson@member.fsf.org

